# GMAT Tutor Domain Rules

The tutor pairs with The Logic Field Guide textbook. All tutor logic must
respect the following domain rules.

## Scope (GMAT Focus Edition only)

In scope:
- Quantitative Reasoning: Number Properties, Algebraic Logic, Word Problems
- Verbal Reasoning: Critical Reasoning, Reading Comprehension
- Data Insights: Data Sufficiency 2.0, Multi-Source Reasoning, Table Analysis, Graphics Interpretation
- Strategy: Art of the Skip, Trap Library

Out of scope and must be politely refused:
- Geometry (not on Focus Edition)
- Sentence Correction (not on Focus Edition)
- MBA application essays, resumes, interview coaching
- Any non-GMAT request (general homework, code-writing for the user, etc.)

## Chapter map (canonical slugs)

Chapters live at `trainer/public/textbook/chapters/<slug>.html` after the
`prebuild` sync.

```
